5 Sec. 4.5. Chapter 209 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
6 thereto a new section to read as follows:
7 The Director may establish, in coordination with the Division
8 of Forestry of the State Department of Conservation and Natural
9 Resources, a transitional housing program for offenders who are:
10 1. Not more than 18 months from eligibility for parole to
11 receive training in forestry management and conservation; and
12 2. Committed to the custody of the Department and eligible
13 for assignment to an institution or facility of minimum security
14 pursuant to the provisions of NRS 209.481.
15 Sec. 5. Chapter 472 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
16 thereto a new section to read as follows:
17 1. The State Forester Firewarden shall establish a hiring
18 program to provide a pathway to hire for firefighting positions
19 within this State. Under the hiring program, the State Forester
20 Firewarden may appoint a person to fill a position in the classified
21 service as a firefighter with the Division of Forestry of the State
22 Department of Conservation and Natural Resources if the person:
23 (a) Was a former offender assigned to work in a program for
24 operating conservation camps established pursuant to NRS
25 209.457 and performed work relating to firefighting;
26 (b) Successfully completed the training necessary to prepare
27 the offenders assigned to the conservation camp to assist in
28 firefighting pursuant to NRS 209.457;
29 (c) Has obtained any certifications required for employment as
30 a firefighter with the Division of Forestry; and
31 (d) Meets any other qualifications established by the State
32 Forester Firewarden.
33 2. The State Forester Firewarden may adopt regulations to
34 carry out the provisions of this section.
